!!! [[0.13.0|https://crosseye.github.io/TW5-SimpleOutlinePlugin/0.13.0/]]

!!!! Minor release (2026-04-17)

```
feat: + tiddler nodes with children; tiddler-label-link; missing-tiddler links
```

* `+` tiddler references can now have indented children.  The node renders as an expandable row: its body (when the tiddler exists and has content) appears in the expanded panel, followed by the child nodes.  This allows every level of a hierarchy — not just the leaves — to be a tiddler.

* New `tiddler-label-link` attribute: makes each tiddler item's label itself a navigation link.  The disclosure arrows remain the sole toggle mechanism.  Navigating to a missing tiddler opens TiddlyWiki's new-tiddler editor, making the outline usable as a top-down scaffold.

* `tiddler-link` glyph is now shown for missing leaf tiddlers (previously suppressed).

* Default CSS now styles `.so-missing` items (italic, muted) and `.so-label-link` anchors, and extends `.so-tiddler-link` to cover leaf rows as well as summary rows.

* New //Cuisine Outline// demo illustrates all three features with a recipe-wiki outline where every level is a tiddler and several entries are deliberately left as placeholders.

